node.text:
Join @PSG players as they get fitted for the formalwear part of their new wardrobe designed by @MrKimJones,
in a partnership that sees Dior become the football team’s official tailor for the next two seasons. The outfits
comprise a cashmere coat, single-breasted jacket, shirt and pants, along with a pair of black leather ‘Dior
Timeless’ cap-toe derbies whose insoles are silver-tone embossed with each player’s number. A tie woven with a ‘Paris Saint-Germain’ logo, cashmere scarf and reversible black and navy belt complete the looks.
#PSGxDior
© @MelindaTriana

- François Demachy, Dior Perfumer-Creator

Accompany her as she gets ready in her plush #DiorChezMoi robe, having fun choosing her beauty look for the day, nipping backstage to @PeterPhilipsMakeup for a final professional finish, and sharing her post-show thoughts.

The book 'Threads of Life: A History of the World Through the Eye of a Needle' proved a starting point for @MariaGraziaChiuri spark for the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2021-2022 collection. And here its author @SewingMatters discusses the overlooked importance of sewing as a millennia-old form of visual communication, a repository for ideas of identity and place, and a means of connecting people and of sharing ideas around the world. 
© Clare Hunter is a community textile artist, curator & author based in Scotland. Threads of Life is published by Sceptre, Hodder & Stoughton (UK), Abrams Press (US), Bollati Boringhieri (Italy) & Uitgeverij Balans (Amsterdam).

node.title: Reclaiming the outsized role of sewing

Uncover the awesome effort required to realize the 340m2 of embroideries that lined the show space for the unveiling of the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2021-2022 collection by @MariaGraziaChiuri. The motifs of artist Eva Jospin's work, 'Chambre de Soie', were divided into panels and interpreted as free-flowing embroideries involving 150 different kinds of stitches and techniques, and undertaken by 300 artisans at the @Chanakya.School in Mumbai, India. Founded in 2017 by the @Chanakya.In ateliers, the school preserves exceptional techniques and empowers women in local communities by training them as master craftspeople, in India a role traditionally reserved for men. This collection is thus a celebration of the transmission and richness of savoir-faire, a collective work glorifying the borderless beauty of craft. 
© Film by @MelindaTriana

Join @PSG players as they get fitted for the formalwear part of their new wardrobe designed by @MrKimJones,
in a partnership that sees Dior become the football team’s official tailor for the next two seasons. The outfits
comprise a cashmere coat, single-breasted jacket, shirt and pants, along with a pair of black leather ‘Dior
Timeless’ cap-toe derbies whose insoles are silver-tone embossed with each player’s number. A tie woven with a ‘Paris Saint-Germain’ logo, cashmere scarf and reversible black and navy belt complete the looks.
#PSGxDior
© @MelindaTriana

Step onto the pitch at Le Parc des Princes with members of the @PSG team as they show off the casual pieces designed by @MrKimJones as part of the club's two-season partnership with Dior. The look is composed of a Harrington jacket, knitted sweater and polo shirt, all adorned with an embroidered 'Paris Saint-Germain' patch and 'CD Icon' initials. Finishing the looks are 'Dior Explorer' derbies in black leather with the iconic #DiorOblique motif and insoles uniquely embossed with each player's number. 
#PSGxDior 
© @MelindaTriana

Get up close with some of the new Dior collection designed by @MrKimJones for the @PSG football team as a number of players arrive at the House to try on their new threads for the first time. Slipping into sleek tailoring, and announcing their positions on the field, are @SergioRamos, @NeymarJr, @Abdou.Lakhad.Diallo, @LeoParedes20, @IamDaniloPereira and @Gigiodonna99.
#PSGxDior
© @MelindaTriana

Marking the unprecedented association of two peerless French names, Dior has created a new wardrobe for the @PSG football team for the next two seasons, mixing #DiorSavoirFaire with contemporary cuts and the use of subtle and refined detailing in both casual and formalwear, all designed by @MrKimJones, Artistic Director of the men's collections. Examples of the tailoring prowess for which the House is justifiably renowned can be seen here on goalkeeper @Gigiodonna99, striker @NeymarJr and midfielder @IamDaniloPereira.
#PSGxDior
© @Brett_Lloyd

Bring a dash of celestial color to your homelife - or brighten up the world outside - with the #DiorChezMoi capsule from #DiorAW21 by @MariaGraziaChiuri. Dress for yourself with #DiorChezMoi from the #DiorAW21 collection by @MariaGraziaChiuri. This covetable capsule extends the 'Zodiac' motif - in different colors, by frequent House collaborator @PietroRuffoArtist - across unerringly elegant and comfortable pieces such as a bathrobe and pajamas as well as #DiorSilk scarves and an embroidered #DiorBookTote for when you need to face the world outside in enviable style.
